   ├── Gatehouse.info
   ├── SidePath
   │   └── DiscardedNote.txt
   └── OuterWalls
       ├── CrumblingTower.look
       ├── StorageRoom
       └── InnerKeep
           ├── GreatHall.info
           ├── OldRecords.tome
           ├── OpenedDoor
           │   └── ForbiddenLibrary
           │       └── ReadingChamber
           │           └── Treasure.txt
           └── StoneKey.key</div>
        </section>
        
        <section class="reflection">
            <h2>What This Assignment Really Was</h2>
            <p>A puzzle inside a story. A game hidden in homework. A riddle made of folders and files.</p>
            <p>I learned that every wrong path taught me something. That reading carefully matters. That asking a friend can change everything. And that sometimes, you have to think just a little bit deeper to find what's truly hidden.</p>
        </section>
        
        <section class="key-points">
            <h3>Key Challenges & Solutions</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Challenge:</strong> Understanding how to use the StoneKey.key file
                <br><strong>Solution:</strong> Learning to use the <code>move</code> command properly</li>
                
                <li><strong>Challenge:</strong> Removing the cursed book
                <br><strong>Solution:</strong> Using the <code>attrib -elim</code> command from the OldRecords.tome</li>
                
                <li><strong>Challenge:</strong> Finding the final treasure
                <br><strong>Solution:</strong> Problem-solving and careful exploration of the ReadingChamber</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
